@* ONE field, BOTH idioms (decision 153): structurally mutated (Add) AND wholesale reassigned
   (Where…ToList). Valid Blazor C# -- the baseline builds -- but the two Filament models collide:
   mutate+version declares `const items` (rows.js), reassign-as-signal needs the field itself to
   be the signal (decision 140). The mixed emission was `const items = […]` then `items = …` -- a
   module that THROWS at the first click. Refused with the split fix until a faithful mapping is
   measured. *@

<button id="add" @onclick="Add">add</button>

<ul id="list">
@foreach (int n in items)
{
    <li @key="n">@n</li>
}
</ul>

@code {
    private List<int> items = new List<int> { 1, 2 };
    private int nextId = 3;

    void Add()
    {
        items.Add(nextId);
        nextId = nextId + 1;
        items = items.Where(x => x != 1).ToList();
    }
}
